SIMPLE: survivorship
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Survivorship
<hw>Sur*viv"or*ship</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state of
being a survivor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The right of a joint tenant, or
other person who has a joint interest in an estate, to take the whole
estate upon the death of other.</def> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Chance of survivorship</b></col>, <cd>the chance that a
person of a given age has of surviving another of a giving age; thus, by
the Carlisle tables of mortality the chances of survivorship for two
persons, aged 25 and 65, are 89 and 11 respectively, or about 8 to 1
that the elder die first.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Susceptibility</ent>⟦br⟧
